name: Albert Avkhadeev
headline: Software engineer
creator: False
bio:
I'm ready to talk about my projects that I'm working on

Kernel TCP Delack Improvement | Linux Kernel, C September 2024 - now.
- As part of my scientific work I am improving the transport layer of the Linux kernel by patching the protocol with a change to the TCP
DELACK mechanism. I am actively studying the structure and principles of the Linux kernel using Tracing tools.
JackRussel | Go, Git October 2023 - October 2023
- I'm developing a CI-cli utility for GIT repositories with the ability to generate a CHANGELOG
document if a linker is connected to fill in conventional commits in a convenient CLI
interface when writing the git commit command
Git Diff Dynamic Web View | Go, Python, Typescript, Git, React September 2023 - September 2023
- This project was completed as part of a hackathon by VK.
- In the team I was developing a client-server application (frontend and backend parts) for
optimal and convenient viewing of the difference between two commits in the repository
- Used pagination method as an optimization on the frontend part
- On the backend used caching to optimize repeated requests
- As a result, we ranked first in our field.
Mockmentor | Python, Pydantic, SQLModel, FastAPI, Git, Bash June 2023 - July 2023
- Developed the backend part of a web application aimed at creating a simulation of a full-blown technical interview using artificial intelligence technologies.
technical interview using artificial intelligence technologies. Used FastAPI as
REST API for the Frontend part on React
- Used SQLModel as a database for storing information about users with the possibility of authorization and registration.
authorization and registration
- I configured the project for deployment on Nginx server.
Music generator | Python, Numpy, Git November 2022 - December 2022
- Wrote a small application that generates an accompaniment for a given melody in the same tonality using gynet technologies.
tonality using gynetic algorithm techniques.

headline: CTO / IT Director / Staff Software Engineer
creator: False
bio:
I am a software engineer with over 10 years of experience in developing enterprise-level, high-performance financial and entertainment services. For the past 7 years, I have specialized in machine learning (ML) systems, and for the last 6 years, I have focused on designing scalable infrastructure services. Over the last 5 years, I have served as a team leader, combining strong leadership with deep technical expertise.

I possess a robust understanding of the software and ML development lifecycle and have successfully implemented and modernized these processes across various teams and projects. My expertise spans software development, ML model training, data analysis, and MLOps/DevOps, enabling me to create products that integrate cutting-edge ML technology with best-in-class software practices while maintaining cost-efficiency and rapid adaptability.

I am currently seeking a new and challenging project where I can continue to grow as an engineer and a leader.

name: Temur Beissov
headline: Software Development Engineer @ SQUIRE | Node.JS, Nest.JS, Javascript, Typescript, Microservices, kafka, redis, docker
creator: False
bio:
üë®‚Äçüíª Backend Engineer | 9+ years of experience

I‚Äôm a Backend Engineer with over 9 years of experience, passionate about building scalable, reliable, and efficient backend systems. My expertise spans software architecture, microservices, and API integrations, allowing me to design and implement solutions that drive business success.

üí° What I Do Best
	‚Ä¢	Backend Development & System Architecture - designing scalable and maintainable systems with a focus on performance and reliability.
	‚Ä¢	Feature Development - implemented key product features like walk-in lists, Stripe‚Äôs instant payouts, and tipping on payment terminals.
	‚Ä¢	API Integrations - worked with Google Places API, Referral Factory, Stripe, and more to enhance product functionality.
	‚Ä¢	Legacy System Optimization - played a key role in fixing all legacy bugs within a month as part of the Alfa team.

üöÄ Beyond Code
	‚Ä¢	Leadership & Mentorship - helping new developers onboard and grow within the team.
	‚Ä¢	Process Improvement - streamlining workflows to boost team efficiency and productivity.
	‚Ä¢	Problem-Solving - analyzing multiple solutions and executing the best approach on time and at scale.

üîç Open to New Opportunities

I love creating solutions that improve daily lives. Seeing my work positively impact users motivates me to deliver high-quality, user-focused products. 
For me, technology is about meaningful innovation, not just code. I thrive in collaborative, learning-driven environments, tackling complex challenges and optimizing systems. Sharing knowledge and leading teams to achieve tangible results is deeply fulfilling. 
I seek a company that values curiosity, teamwork, and impactful products.

name: Naghme Mohammadifar
headline: DevOps Engineer passionate about development, automation & cloud technologies
creator: False
bio:
Driven by a passion for technology and a fervent curiosity for innovation, my journey in IT commenced with a solid educational foundation in Security and Network Engineering from Innopolis University for my Master's and Ferdowsi University for my Bachelor's in Computer Engineering.

My career voyage began with a practical immersion in programming, web, and backend development‚Äîa realm I explored out of sheer passion. However, my penchant for infrastructure was undeniable. This inclination led me to my current role as a DevOps Tech Support Engineer in a multinational corporation, where I've delved into the intricate fusion of development and operations, leveraging my comprehensive understanding of both domains.

Eager to broaden my expertise, I've pursued diverse internships, honing my skills in cloud, security, infrastructure, and system design. Engaging with the Security Lab at Ferdowsi University further fortified my practical understanding.

As an example, my master's thesis explored the profound potential of blockchain within a secure online examination system, underlining my enthusiasm for security and relentless pursuit of emerging technologies.

Alongside my professional journey, I've embraced teaching, sharing my knowledge as a Teaching Assistant for Java, C programming, System Design, and Analysis during my bachelor's and, later, guiding students in Distributed Systems and DevOps courses at Innopolis University. Teaching programming languages to young minds at 'Geeklama' was an immensely rewarding experience.

I thrive in collaborative environments and have seamlessly integrated within cross-functional teams, enabling successful project outcomes. From collaborating closely with developers on infrastructure setup to delivering ongoing support and troubleshooting, I'm deeply committed to fostering open lines of communication and promoting teamwork. I thoroughly enjoy working as a team player and engaging with diverse individuals to achieve our collective goals.

Continuously seeking growth and improvement, I remain dedicated to staying updated with the latest industry trends and technologies. My passion for continuous learning has fueled my exploration of emerging DevOps practices, such as infrastructure as code, serverless architectures, and cloud-native deployments. This commitment to staying at the forefront of technology drives my ability to adapt to evolving industry demands.

name: Nataliya Matrosova
headline: Golang backend dev
creator: False
bio:
I am doing backend in a micro-service architecture for OZON Bank and I am thrilled about it c:

Currently I am working at Ozon.ru as a backend-software engineer on Golang.

I am using PostgreSQL on a daily basis. 
Use Grafana & Prometeus for monitoring. Gitlab & Gitlab-CI.

I design and develop services for architecture in a banking sphere. 

Here the highlight of the most importsnt services I developed:
1. Recounciliations: compares payment requisites among several services and highlights differences for the accountants. That one is one of the most importance.
Any budget mismatch could potentially result in a fine or loss of income, so this particular service literally saves company‚Äôa money per each difference found.

2. library-service: this one is a high load service that stores mappings from one financial codes to another. Such kind of information is crucial for services inside the banking circuit, so it is often requested when performing bank transfers.


I used to work as Python Software Develope in Machine Learning data preprocessing. Mostly using Python language + numpy, scipy, matplotlib and data annotation tools like supervise.ly. I have distributed system managing experience with AWS VPC, docker swarm clusters as well. 

Bs in Computer Science.
Erasmus+ graduate: Computer Science at TU Dublin (Ireland, Republic of). 
Fluent in English and Russian. 

I enjoy cycling, running and playing strategic board games as a hobby.

feel free to contact me on LinkedIn.
Open to backend position with relocation package.

bio:
As a believer in the transformative potential of technology, I am deeply passionate about DevOps/Cloud, Cybersecurity, and Software Engineering. With a dedication to staying at the forefront of these rapidly evolving fields for more than 5 years, I am constantly honing my skills and knowledge to ensure that I can deliver the very best results for my clients and colleagues.

In addition to my work in the tech industry, I am also an article writer on Medium & an open-source contributor at devops-journey.uz where I mostly tend to write about DevOps, CI/CD, AWS, and Cybersecurity. Moreover, I am the alumni of SSI 20', Huawei SFTF 23', and the scholar of JACAFA TNF 22'.
